  # Zulu
  
  The ZSH Environment Manager
  
  ```sh
  curl -L https://zulu.molovo.co/install | zsh && zsh
  ```
  
  ## Features
  
  Choose from a wide range of packages, including plugins, autoloadable ZSH modules and standalone applications.
  
  ```
  fzf-git                   -- A plugin which sets up git keybindings for    fzf-marks                 -- Little script to create  navigate and dele    git                       -- A selection of handy git aliases              gitignore                 -- ZSH plugin for creating .gitignore files      gitio                     -- A zsh plugin for generating a GitHub short    gnu-utility               -- Provides for the interactive use of GNU ut    history-substring-search  -- ZSH port of Fish shell's history search fe    history-sync              -- plugin for synced zsh_history; with encryp    homebrew                  -- Aliases and functions for homebrew            insert-sudo               -- A little zsh snippet to prepend sudo to th    k                         -- k is the new l  yo                            load-graph                -- Outputs the current 1-minute load average     lumberjack                -- A logging interface for shell scripts         node                      -- Aliases and functions for node                nvm-auto-use              -- ZSH plugin to call `nvm use` automatically    osx                       -- macOS related functions                       pretty-time               -- Convert seconds to a human readable string    pure                      -- Pretty  minimal and fast ZSH prompt           rbenv                     -- ruby/rails aliases; rbenv init                revolver                  -- A progress spinner for shell scripts          39/45     matches
  ```
  
