  # Zulu
  
  [Permalink: Zulu](https://github.com/zulu-zsh/zulu/blob/master/README.md#zulu)
  
  Zulu: [![GitHub release](https://camo.githubusercontent.com/c1759f9e215344fe15f8c88498cd82b0befc26d70d8c1ed7df9fb1c53b4c63d8/68747470733a2f2f696d672e736869656c64732e696f2f6769746875622f72656c656173652f7a756c752d7a73682f7a756c752e737667)](https://github.com/zulu-zsh/zulu/releases/latest)[![Build Status](https://camo.githubusercontent.com/4b227d9a83670293bcd1a6ed541efc073afc3bafde6ee57a94666bb2a5fe689c/68747470733a2f2f7472617669732d63692e6f72672f7a756c752d7a73682f7a756c752e7376673f6272616e63683d6d6173746572)](https://travis-ci.org/zulu-zsh/zulu) \| Index: [![Build Status](https://camo.githubusercontent.com/80ef612d0fc79df0de87dc84ce30a500ba638a87e49c70d2e7a0e47fcb4f0346/68747470733a2f2f7472617669732d63692e6f72672f7a756c752d7a73682f696e6465782e7376673f6272616e63683d6d6173746572)](https://travis-ci.org/zulu-zsh/index) \| [![Join the chat at https://gitter.im/zulu-zsh/zulu](https://camo.githubusercontent.com/81af4215f20b761d17dd7aad8321190485189c19e136b98915d0ca9aff53603c/68747470733a2f2f6261646765732e6769747465722e696d2f7a756c752d7a73682f7a756c752e737667)](https://gitter.im/zulu-zsh/zulu?utm_source=badge&utm_medium=badge&utm_campaign=pr-badge&utm_content=badge)
  
  Thanks for using Zulu. Zulu is a environment manager for ZSH, which aims to make it easy to manage your shell without writing any code.
  
  ## Features
  
  [Permalink: Features](https://github.com/zulu-zsh/zulu/blob/master/README.md#features)
  
  - Easily manage your shell environment without editing files.
  - Create aliases, functions and environment variables, and have them available to you at the next shell startup.
  - Add and remove directories from `$path`, `$fpath` and `$cdpath` with simple commands.
  - Install packages, plugins and themes easily, and have them available to you immediately.
  
  ## Requirements
  
  [Permalink: Requirements](https://github.com/zulu-zsh/zulu/blob/master/README.md#requirements)
  
  - ZSH `5.0.2` or above
  - git `1.9.1` or above
  
  ## Installation
  
  [Permalink: Installation](https://github.com/zulu-zsh/zulu/blob/master/README.md#installation)
  
  Zulu comes with its own install script, which is the recommended method of install.
  
  ```
  curl -L https://zulu.molovo.co/install | zsh && zsh
  ```
  
  If you'd rather not pipe a script into ZSH, take a look at the [manual installation process](https://zulu.molovo.co/docs/getting-started/manual-installation).
  
  ## Usage
  
  [Permalink: Usage](https://github.com/zulu-zsh/zulu/blob/master/README.md#usage)
  
  For detailed usage instructions, take a look at Zulu's [official documentation](https://zulu.molovo.co/docs)
  
